#	Config file for the Poisson Multigrid module that couples to the AMUSE astrophysics package.
#   Written by Josh Wall, Drexel U.  
#  [source/physics/Gravity/Poisson/Multigrid/Couple_AMUSE]

PPDEFINE AMUSE_GRAVITY_BRIDGE

REQUESTS Grid/GridSolvers/Multigrid

# Runtime parameters
REQUESTS Grid/GridSolvers/IsoBndMultipole


# These variables are used to map the accelerations
# at each point in the grid to the sinks in the simulation.
# These accels are gathered in Gravity_accelOneRow (which is
# called by the hydro solver) or in Gravity_accelOneBlock if
# its called.
# These possibly no longer needed with PM bridge. - JW
#VARIABLE gacx
#VARIABLE gacy
#VARIABLE gacz
#VARIABLE gaox
#VARIABLE gaoy
#VARIABLE gaoz

# This is the potential variable for the sinks gravity on the gas.
# Used for the new particle mesh mapping method of the gravity bridge.
# This gets finite differenced to get the acceleration for the bridge
# for the sinks gravity on the gas.

#VARIABLE SGPT

# For the PM bridge used in AMUSE coupling - JW
D BGPT The gravitational potential from the particles on the gas.
VARIABLE BGPT
D And acceleration variables for the acceleration from the particles on the gas.
D (Because using the sink ones doesnt work if we are including sinks and massive particles.)
VARIABLE BGAX
VARIABLE BGAY
VARIABLE BGAZ
